The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                State transport minister Ranjit Kundu on Monday met the managing directors and union leaders of five state-owned transport corporations to discuss the proposed early retirement scheme (ERS) for the employees. The scheme will help the corporations to replace physically unfit employees with new recruits.  undu said ERS benefits would be offered taking into consideration the number of years the employee spent in the organisation or the number of years of service left, whichever is higher. The unions have been asked for their opinion. We want to start the process soon, he said.    Five men were arrested in Titagarh on Sunday night when they were allegedly planning a robbery. Two firearms, five bullets and two daggers were seized from them.    A fire broke out in an AC machine in SSKM Hospitals burn unit around 9.30pm on Monday. The flames were doused by hospital employees.    Kamal Sapui, 28, was arrested at Joynagar, on the southern fringes of the city, on Sunday night for allegedly stealing a gold chain from her employers house on September 15. Sapui worked as a help in the Karaya house of Chandranarayan Bhattacharya, the director of the Central Forensic Science Laboratory. The chain has been recovered.    The high court on Monday admitted a petition by green activist Subhash Dutta seeking an order directing the civic body and Calcutta Port Trust to keep the Hooghly clean during idol immersion in the festive season.    The body of Raju Chandra, a 44-year-old Howrah resident, was found floating in a pond at Chandmari on Monday.                                                                                                                                              
